                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.511,
                                "byte_start": 104448,
                                "byte_stop": 142587,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion this morning in Case 10-8974, Perry versus New Hampshire."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.511,
                        "stop": 305.659,
                        "byte_start": 142587,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.511,
                                "stop": 39.983,
                                "byte_start": 142587,
                                "byte_stop": 264422,
                                "text": "Suppose the police arrange a lineup in which only the suspect is made to wear distinctive clothes and an eyewitness then picks the suspect out of the lineup, police arranged suggestive circumstances, we have held, called for a due process check before allowing the jury to hear the identification evidence, the trial judge must screen it for reliability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.983,
                                "stop": 56.865,
                                "byte_start": 264422,
                                "byte_stop": 331922,
                                "text": "The petitioner in this case, Barion Perry, asks us to extend judicial preview of eyewitness identifications to all suggestive circumstances not just those organized by the police."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.865,
                                "stop": 62.754,
                                "byte_start": 331922,
                                "byte_stop": 355537,
                                "text": "For reasons explained in the opinion filed today, we decline to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.754,
                                "stop": 72.356,
                                "byte_start": 355537,
                                "byte_stop": 393885,
                                "text": "Petitioner Perry was arrested for theft after an eyewitness identified him as the man she had just seen breaking in to a car."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.356,
                                "stop": 79.403,
                                "byte_start": 393885,
                                "byte_stop": 422097,
                                "text": "At the time of the identification, Perry was standing in a parking lot next to a police officer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.403,
                                "stop": 82.884,
                                "byte_start": 422097,
                                "byte_stop": 435994,
                                "text": "Perry moved to suppress the identification."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.884,
                                "stop": 90.209,
                                "byte_start": 435994,
                                "byte_stop": 465356,
                                "text": "Admitting it at a trial, he argued, would be fundamentally unfair and therefore a denial of due process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.209,
                                "stop": 98.361,
                                "byte_start": 465356,
                                "byte_stop": 497957,
                                "text": "No improper police conduct, Perry conceded, tainted the identification in his case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.361,
                                "stop": 102.69,
                                "byte_start": 497957,
                                "byte_stop": 515302,
                                "text": "The New Hampshire trial court denied the supression motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.69,
                                "stop": 110.848,
                                "byte_start": 515302,
                                "byte_stop": 547903,
                                "text": "Perry was tried and convicted and the New Hampshire Supreme Court upheld both the ruling on motion and Perry\u2019s conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.848,
                                "stop": 113.883,
                                "byte_start": 547903,
                                "byte_stop": 560024,
                                "text": "We affirm the state court judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.883,
                                "stop": 133.372,
                                "byte_start": 560024,
                                "byte_stop": 637973,
                                "text": "In every case, in which we have invoked due process to require a trial judge to prescreen identification evidence, law enforcement officials had arranged the suggested -- suggestive circumstances that may have influenced the identification."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.372,
                                "stop": 147.513,
                                "byte_start": 637973,
                                "byte_stop": 694502,
                                "text": "Perry so acknowledges, but urges a broader rule one requiring trial judges to preview eyewitness evidence in any and all suggestive circumstances whether or not police are involved."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.513,
                                "stop": 159.792,
                                "byte_start": 694502,
                                "byte_stop": 743717,
                                "text": "A prime reason for excluding identification evidence generated by police under unnecessarily suggestive circumstances is deterrence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.792,
                                "stop": 176.006,
                                "byte_start": 743717,
                                "byte_stop": 808500,
                                "text": "The aim is to stop law enforcement officers from using improper arrangements, for example, suggestive lineups, showups or photo arrays where there is no improper police conduct, there is nothing to deter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.006,
                                "stop": 203.075,
                                "byte_start": 808500,
                                "byte_stop": 916752,
                                "text": "External suggestion is hardly the only factor that can cast out on the trustworthiness of an eyewitness\u0027 testimony, an eyewitness with poor vision or one who harbors a grudge against the defendant is not inherently more reliable then one who makes an identification under suggestive circumstances, but Perry does not ask us to extend pretrial screening that far."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 203.075,
                                "stop": 215.899,
                                "byte_start": 916752,
                                "byte_stop": 968056,
                                "text": "He maintains that eyewitness identifications made under suggestive circumstances are a uniquely unreliable form of evidence and so, should be treated as a special category."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.899,
                                "stop": 237.49,
                                "byte_start": 968056,
                                "byte_stop": 1054469,
                                "text": "We do not doubt either the fallibility or the importance of eyewitness evidence generally or the caution appropriate whenever suggestive circumstances may have influenced an identification, but in our system of justice, the jury, not the judge, ordinarily determines the trustworthiness of the evidence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.49,
                                "stop": 249.952,
                                "byte_start": 1054469,
                                "byte_stop": 1104311,
                                "text": "Safeguards are built into our system that can serve to inhibit juries from placing undue weight on eyewitness and other testimony of questionable reliability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 249.952,
                                "stop": 269.556,
                                "byte_start": 1104311,
                                "byte_stop": 1182678,
                                "text": "These protections, many of them at work in Perry\u2019s trial, include the defendant\u0027s Sixth Amendment right to counsel, to confront and cross-examine witnesses, eyewitness specific jury instructions and the constitutional requirement that the defendant\u0027s guilt be proved beyond a reasonable doubt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 269.556,
                                "stop": 286.768,
                                "byte_start": 1182678,
                                "byte_stop": 1251537,
                                "text": "State and federal rules of evidence, moreover, arm trial judges with discretion to exclude relevant evidence if its probative value is substantially outweighed by its prejudicial impact or potential for misleading the jury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 286.768,
                                "stop": 297.885,
                                "byte_start": 1251537,
                                "byte_stop": 1296050,
                                "text": "Absent improper police conduct, these safeguards, we hold, keep the introduction of eyewitness identification evidence within constitutional bounds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 297.885,
                                "stop": 300.923,
                                "byte_start": 1296050,
                                "byte_stop": 1308170,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a concurring opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 300.923,
                                "stop": 305.659,
                                "byte_start": 1308170,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
